1.  **`trickle_fsync_interval_in_kb`**: This parameter is used in the `maybeFsync` and `maybeSkipCache` methods. In `maybeFsync`, it determines the interval (in kilobytes) at which the system performs an `fsync` operation to flush data to disk. In `maybeSkipCache`, it serves as a threshold to decide whether to skip the page cache for a file, based on its size.
2.  **`disk_access_mode`**: This parameter is used in the `BigTableWriter` constructor to configure the `FileHandle.Builder`. Specifically, it checks if the `disk_access_mode` is set to `mmap` (memory-mapped I/O) to determine how the data file should be accessed.

These configurations directly influence the I/O behavior and performance of the system, particularly in terms of data persistence and memory management.

